##Is there a way out of the epidemic for brick-and-mortar bookstores other than to call for help and shut down?

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

In the past, online shops, online shops selling coffee, purely by selling books to solve the down-to-earth, but now, they are "dead" .

Journalist | Chang Peak, intern | Chen Ganbo, editor | Shen Xiaolu

Finally, a store.

The past month has been a 30-day crisis for self-employed brick-and-mortar bookstores. On February 5th an analysis of an emergency survey of brick and mortar bookstores for the 2020 Lunar New Year holiday was released, covering 1,021 first tier cities and 80% of second, third tier and more sinking bookstores, 90% of which were closed and 99% had no regular revenue.

Of course, the impact of the epidemic is not only the loss of revenue during the peak season of the Spring Festival, but also the strain on cash flow, which has directly accelerated the discussion of "how to live" : In the past, online red shops sold coffee across the Internet, just rely on selling books to settle down, but now, they are "dead" .

It's a shame that the bookstore has to "save the poor" . That's the problem with its business model, but "save the emergency" is the way it has to be done

On Feb. 20, Qingyuan Bookstore, one of the cultural landmarks in Nanchang, Jiangxi Province, welcomed its first book club in 2020 -- a crowd of online wechat readers with the theme of "What can reading bring us? "

You can imagine a group of over 200 people, who have lost public space, who are in their closed homes, with their legs crossed, holding books and listening to voices, who have been called away and temporarily shut down, who have been forced away to feed their babies, the organizers don't know how many people are actually listening, but the good news is, someone is.

Qingyuan is probably one of the first independent bookstores to publicly ask readers for help online. On the last day of January, when the epidemic was at its worst and most chaotic, Wan Guoying, the owner, published an article on his public account entitled "I am Qingyuan Bookstore, please don't let me freeze to death in the wind and snow. " He launched a 200-2,000-yuan top-up card business, "please lend a helping hand" to cash flow.

Wan didn't say how bad the loss was. In fact, the store spent more than 300,000 yuan a month. At the end of the year, it had just settled accounts with publishers and suppliers, plus an advance on a batch of new books, plus year-end bonuses for employees, there's only a little over a hundred grand left in January's account.

A customer wearing a mask at Qingyuan bookstore

Thinking of at least a cut for the Spring Festival, Wan Guoying continued the tradition of taking only two days off a year: The 30th day of the Lunar New Year and the first day of the Lunar New Year, it's better not to have a shop. A few days later, the government issued a document barring businesses from operating until Feb. 10, after which the opening of stores was delayed and delayed.

"We are in the cultural services industry, the last ones to go back to work. Companies are helping themselves, and the government says they can report the outbreak and apply for a month-to-month-and-a-half rent-free. That's all for the future, and I don't know what kind of trouble I'm going to run into."

Far Water can not quench near thirst, 28 years since the opening of the shop, Wan Guoying for the first time Green Garden "survive" worry.

Also seeking help online is Guangzhou's cultural label "1200 bookshop" . The Independent Bookstore, which in 2015 was named by CNN as one of the 17 coolest bookstores in the world, has kept its lights on since it opened, is open 24 hours a day, and regularly invites security guards and homeless singers to give talks, the late-night sharing session, held every Saturday night at 12 pm, has become one of the most talked-about stores on social media for "falling in love with a city because of a bookstore. ". Of course, all the charm comes from the offline, the store door closed, almost blocked everything.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Activities have always been featured in 1200 bookshop / Sweet John

Liu Erxi, the founder of 1200, and his team are younger. In addition to stored value cards, they have also made "blind selection book gift bags" and cultural and creative products. They have more gestures to save emergencies. In less than two days, they have raised more than 400,000 yuan, and can last two more months.

Liu Acknowledges the advantages of this "fan economy. " In the past few years, 1200 has been expanding, opening new stores almost every year, from individual to corporate operations, putting the money back into new projects, it may be partly responsible for the 1200's vulnerability.

The reality of the chain is under control, said Zhou Juan, director of public affairs at Yanji, who said in some surveys that big companies may be "worse off. ". Yanji also directly operated stores and franchise stores during the epidemic passenger flow suffered a precipitous decline, stores lost 95% of turnover. Even if the first time line launched a "city distribution" remedial measures, Zhou Juan also admitted that the short-term effect is difficult to judge, but made efforts, can not do nothing.

Yanji has reached 1000 square meters in the average area of shops in major cities across the country, and the rent has become the largest expenditure. The government's advice on rent reduction is instructive, and the negotiation with the main shopping mall is only "tentative. ".

In the first 10 months of 2019, YAN JI had sales of 600 million yuan, ranking second among the top 10 bookstores in China, according to public figures.

Those who are willing to speak up and try to change are, after all, a few. Many more are scattered around the fourth and fifth tier cities, on Street corners in obscurity, as if time had stood still, doing what they do best and dying quietly.

50% off on the internet. Would you pay for a full-price book for "atmosphere" ?

In fact, brick and mortar bookstores are like chronic disease patients who don't want to leave. The epidemic is just a catalyst, and in the past year, it's gotten worse.

Wan Guoying from the second half of 2018 began to feel the physical bookstore nearly five years of short spring has passed. From the annual "618" , "double 11" and "double 12" to the quarterly discount, e-commerce platforms have been offering promotional discounts almost every month since 2019.

"The discount is so great that all my friends go online to buy them. The Zhonghua Book Company and the triple couplets are 38 to 42 percent off, and we and the publishing house can't even get in at that price. The business gives us 68 percent off, and the triple couplets are 65 percent off. How can we compete? "

Retail sales in brick and mortar bookstores fell 7.68 percent in 2019, while online sales grew 24.7 percent, according to an industry survey by Wan Guoying. That includes big, state owned enterprises like Xinhua Bookstore.

These declines are due to changes in the structure of the book itself and to a shift in the focus of publishers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qing Yuan Bookstore during the outbreak

Xinhua Bookstore found that sales of social books rose 30% to 40% of the company's growth, with the majority of that coming from party books. In Jiangxi Province, where WAN is based, the proportion of party books in the Xinhua Bookstore has even reached 50% . If you strip out the earmarks for government departments, the decline in brick-and-mortar bookstores is much bigger than before.

At the same time, there are "fewer and fewer" books to choose from. According to the China Book Market Report 2019, the number of new titles published in 2019 was only 80 percent of that in 2018. No one can expect to sell 100 titles for 80 titles for 100 prices and sales.

Publishers, which are closely related to brick and mortar bookstores, are moving away from brick and mortar bookstores and toward online platforms, and their sales role in brick and mortar bookstores is declining. According to wgb understanding, there are e-commerce platform mandatory fixed profit and return point requirements, publishers want to get sales volume and visibility of the rise, can only be passively accepted.

One way publishers are moving away from platform constraints is to operate their own online stores, which are still heavily discounted. At the flagship store of Commercial Press, the 2020 edition of the dictionary is priced at 99.8 yuan, 49.9 yuan at a discount, 3 yuan off the immediate order, and nearly 100 yuan off the line for readers to buy directly from the publisher for only 46.9 yuan.

This has created a new situation, online platforms and publishing houses squeeze Physical Bookstore Living Space, publishing house profits damage to open a store alone, publishing to do more and more things, and blurred the upstream and downstream relationship, the bookstore as a simple place to put books, become more and more awkward.

Under pressure WGB has started to try something it never would have done before: Participating in project tenders. Help the university library select books. And the General Library, the university library tender, was basically taken away by the Xinhua Bookstore.

At the same time, the business of Wenchuang and coffee contributes to some of the revenue. They all say you can diversify and do more.

Where's the energy to do anything else, you're not good at what you do I'm just a shop owner

The shop is open and people are still calling for help

In the full resumption of the first day of work, adhere to the 15-year one-way Street Bookstore Article "crowdfunding life" , founder Xu Zhiyuan could not resist.

1200 store opened, the impact of the epidemic has not yet dispersed, still not many people, up to twenty "warriors" , guests to shoot the shop video, more direct, buy books, walk, the transaction rate instead up. Albert Camus bought out the stock, and before that the best was Hu Shih's tolerance and freedom.

1200 bookshop by Fanfan

The clerk took a short video at the sports store and put a sign with the word "power" in red on it into a bird cage to make a new "pet" .

1200 bookshop is still exploring "character" and "freedom" , finding a balance between business and value. The cultural value of "blind selection" and "pharmacy" for books not only gives readers a sense of freshness, but also drives sales.

To sum up, why can I get huge fan support in time of crisis? Liu Er felt that 1200 may be more humane and down-to-earth compared with the high-and-mighty bookstore, and the other is youth attribute, it's like the collective spirit of the Beat Generation.

The outbreak has made 1,200's director of books, Adoi Hai, realize that the online trend was "unstoppable. " But all he could think of was to open an online bookstore to sell books in a limited time, or run a wechat group. Sun Qian, a well-known bookstore owner, said in his live broadcast about the future of the bookstore in the new context, using the most popular language nowadays: "The bookstore should run its own private traffic. "

Wan Guoying is still worried that bookstores are still facing deadly pressure to survive. This epidemic affects not only bookstores, but also publishing houses. It is inevitable that after production resumes, they will have to reduce inventory and increase discounts. This is a business rule for her, and there's no solution.

She worries that brick-and-mortar bookshops will not be able to survive the disaster.

"economic things can be made up for later, but in the construction and deposition of civilization, cultural attributes may be silent. "

Wan also wants to bring in more popular science books on music and medicine, and a reading list on psychology. "because after this epidemic, I'm sure many people have some fluctuations in their emotions, some worries about the future, and in the area of medical science and technology, and emotional health, Qingyuan can do something. "
